other_tests.findings: Partial intrasellar arachnoidocele, hypoplastic anterior pituitary, ectopic posterior pituitary lobe (EPP), absent pituitary stalk, and thin anterior corpus callosum.
Identified two PROKR2 mutations (p.Leu173Arg and p.Arg85His) and a novel PROKR2 variant (p.Ala51Thr) that did not impair receptor signaling activity.
Three allelic variants of HESX1 identified: p.Phe156Ser and p.Arg109X mutations were functionally deleterious, whereas p.Ser67Thr was a rare variant in association with p.Arg85His PROKR2 mutation.

other_tests.changes_over_time: ACTH deficiency and hypogonadotroph hypogonadism diagnosed at 23 months and 14 years, respectively.

other_tests.findings: Showed EPP, pituitary stalk interruption, and porencephaly.
